overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate its implementation against the project's
  Statement of Work and detailed questionnaire specifications. The agent
  performed an in-depth analysis of the codebase, identifying several areas
  where the current implementation fell short of the requirements. Following
  this assessment, a prioritized action plan was formulated. The agent then
  proceeded to implement the highest priority items, successfully integrating a
  1-10 severity scale for tiredness, complete with critical safety warnings for
  high scores. Additionally, the agent implemented the detection and reporting
  of Comorbid Insomnia and Sleep Apnea (COMISA), providing specific diagnostic
  messages and recommendations in both the interactive report and the generated
  PDF. These enhancements significantly improve the questionnaire's diagnostic
  accuracy and user safety guidance.
